==Korean==
===Noun===
'''구멍''' (gumeong)

#[[hole]]
#*바지에 '''구멍'''이 났다. (''baji-e gumeong-i nattda''.) <br> [I’ve] got a hole in my trousers. <br> Literally, "A hole appeared in my trousers."
#*벽에 '''구멍'''을 뚫다. (''byeog-e '''gumeong'''eul ttulhda'') <br> To drill a '''hole''' in a wall.

====Related terms====
*[[오존]] 구멍 (''ojon gumeong'') &mdash; ozone hole
*[[검]]은 구멍 (''geom-eun gumeong'') &mdash; [[black hole]]

====Synonyms====
* [[구무]] (gumu) (obsolete) [[hole]], [[hollow]], [[cave]]  
* [[굳]] (gud, gut) (obsolete) [[hole]], [[hollow]], [[cave]], cf. [[gut]] or [[alimentary canal]]  
* [[굼]] (gum) (obsolete) [[hole]], [[hollow]], [[cave]]  
* [[굿]] (gus) (obsolete) [[hole]], [[hollow]], [[cave]] 
* [[구덩이]] (gudeongI) [[pit]], [[hollow]]
* [[구렁]] (gureong) [[pit]], [[hollow]]
* [[굴]] (gul) [[cave]]; [[tunnel]]; [[hole]], [[hollow]]; [[den]], [[burrow]]; cf. [[gullet]], [[gully]]

